cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with decision trees and randomized forests, which are widely used in machine learning. It also presents an algorithm for optimizing the split functions at all levels of the tree jointly with the leaf parameters, based on a global objective. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as decision trees and randomized forests are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object recognition and image segmentation.

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as decision trees are a popular method in AI for classification and prediction tasks.

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as decision trees are a data structure used for organizing and representing data.

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely sub-category as decision trees can be used in network analysis and modeling, but this paper does not focus on that application.
